spec: threading_extra55
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(threading)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/threading.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/threading.html — Python threading module documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/threading.py"
    - "CPython source: Modules/_threadmodule.c"
  notes:
    - "This spec extends threading_extra54.zspec.zsdl."
    - "Prior specs covered __dict__.__class__.__name__.__len__()==12 for Thread/Event/Timer/Barrier/Condition/Semaphore (one set of specs) and Semaphore/BoundedSemaphore (another set). No prior threading spec records __dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('mappingproxy') as an explicit invariant row for any threading class."
    - "No prior threading spec records __dict__.__class__.__qualname__.__eq__('mappingproxy') for any threading class."
    - "Prior specs covered threading function __qualname__.__eq__ for main_thread/current_thread/active_count/enumerate/settrace/setprofile/stack_size (threading_extra15/extra22/extra47). No prior threading spec records __qualname__.__len__() for any of these functions."
    - "This spec covers: threading.Thread.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('mappingproxy')==true; threading.Event.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('mappingproxy')==true; threading.Semaphore.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('mappingproxy')==true; threading.Condition.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('mappingproxy')==true; threading.Barrier.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('mappingproxy')==true; threading.Timer.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('mappingproxy')==true; threading.Thread.__dict__.__class__.__qualname__.__eq__('mappingproxy')==true; threading.Event.__dict__.__class__.__qualname__.__eq__('mappingproxy')==true; threading.main_thread.__qualname__.__len__()==11; threading.current_thread.__qualname__.__len__()==14; threading.active_count.__qualname__.__len__()==12."
    - "Key findings: Python class __dict__ is always a mappingproxy whose type is builtins.mappingproxy. mappingproxy.__name__ == 'mappingproxy' (12 chars) and mappingproxy.__qualname__ == 'mappingproxy' (12 chars; top-level type). Prior threading specs only recorded the length (12) via __len__(), not the string equality form. The __qualname__ form is entirely new. Additionally, threading function __qualname__ values equal their __name__ (top-level functions, no enclosing class scope): main_thread (11 chars), current_thread (14 chars), active_count (12 chars). Prior specs confirmed the string equality values but no prior spec records their __len__() as explicit invariant rows. All eleven invariants are new to extra55."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
  created_at: "2026-04-10T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# threading class __dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy' — extra55
#
# All pure-Python threading classes (Thread, Event, Semaphore, Condition,
# Barrier, Timer) store their class namespace in a __dict__ that is a
# mappingproxy object. The mappingproxy type is builtins.mappingproxy, and
# mappingproxy.__name__ == 'mappingproxy' (12 chars). Prior threading specs
# recorded __dict__.__class__.__name__.__len__()==12 for all these classes but
# no prior spec records the string equality form .__eq__('mappingproxy') for
# any threading class. All six checks below are new to extra55.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table threading_extra55.class_dict_class_name_eq:
  description: "threading class __dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy' — class __dict__ is a mappingproxy; mappingproxy.__name__ == 'mappingproxy' (12 chars); prior specs recorded __len__()==12; string equality form is new to extra55"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: identity
  id_prefix: thrddict55

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - [Thread_dict_class_name,
       Thread.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__,
       ["mappingproxy"],
       true,
       "threading.Thread.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy' — Thread is a pure-Python class in Lib/threading.py that represents a thread of control; its __dict__ is a mappingproxy (Python's read-only class namespace wrapper); mappingproxy.__name__ == 'mappingproxy' (12 chars); prior specs confirmed Thread.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__len__()==12 but did not record the string equality; this is the first __dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('mappingproxy') row for Thread; new to extra55"]
    - [Event_dict_class_name,
       Event.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__,
       ["mappingproxy"],
       true,
       "threading.Event.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy' — Event is a pure-Python class in Lib/threading.py implementing a thread synchronization primitive using an internal flag; its __dict__ is a mappingproxy; mappingproxy.__name__ == 'mappingproxy' (12 chars); prior specs confirmed Event.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__len__()==12 but did not record the string equality; this is the first __dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('mappingproxy') row for Event; new to extra55"]
    - [Semaphore_dict_class_name,
       Semaphore.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__,
       ["mappingproxy"],
       true,
       "threading.Semaphore.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy' — Semaphore is a pure-Python class in Lib/threading.py implementing a counting semaphore for thread synchronization; its __dict__ is a mappingproxy; mappingproxy.__name__ == 'mappingproxy' (12 chars); prior specs confirmed Semaphore.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__len__()==12 but did not record the string equality; this is the first __dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('mappingproxy') row for Semaphore; new to extra55"]
    - [Condition_dict_class_name,
       Condition.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__,
       ["mappingproxy"],
       true,
       "threading.Condition.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy' — Condition is a pure-Python class in Lib/threading.py implementing a condition variable for complex thread synchronization; its __dict__ is a mappingproxy; mappingproxy.__name__ == 'mappingproxy' (12 chars); prior specs confirmed Condition.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__len__()==12 but did not record the string equality; this is the first __dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('mappingproxy') row for Condition; new to extra55"]
    - [Barrier_dict_class_name,
       Barrier.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__,
       ["mappingproxy"],
       true,
       "threading.Barrier.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy' — Barrier is a pure-Python class in Lib/threading.py that allows a fixed number of threads to synchronize at a common point; its __dict__ is a mappingproxy; mappingproxy.__name__ == 'mappingproxy' (12 chars); prior specs confirmed Barrier.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__len__()==12 but did not record the string equality; this is the first __dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('mappingproxy') row for Barrier; new to extra55"]
    - [Timer_dict_class_name,
       Timer.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__,
       ["mappingproxy"],
       true,
       "threading.Timer.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy' — Timer is a pure-Python class in Lib/threading.py (Thread subclass that executes a function after a specified delay); its __dict__ is a mappingproxy; mappingproxy.__name__ == 'mappingproxy' (12 chars); prior specs confirmed Timer.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__len__()==12 but did not record the string equality; this is the first __dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('mappingproxy') row for Timer; new to extra55"]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# threading class __dict__.__class__.__qualname__ == 'mappingproxy' — extra55
#
# The mappingproxy type is a top-level type in the builtins module with no
# enclosing class scope, so its __qualname__ == __name__ == 'mappingproxy'
# (12 chars). No prior threading spec records __dict__.__class__.__qualname__
# for any threading class. The two checks below establish this new dimension.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table threading_extra55.class_dict_class_qualname_eq:
  description: "threading class __dict__.__class__.__qualname__ == 'mappingproxy' — mappingproxy is a top-level type so __qualname__ == __name__ == 'mappingproxy' (12 chars); __qualname__ form not recorded in any prior threading spec"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: identity
  id_prefix: thrddict55

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - [Thread_dict_class_qualname,
       Thread.__dict__.__class__.__qualname__.__eq__,
       ["mappingproxy"],
       true,
       "threading.Thread.__dict__.__class__.__qualname__ == 'mappingproxy' — Thread's class __dict__ is a mappingproxy; the mappingproxy type is a top-level type with __qualname__ == __name__ == 'mappingproxy' (12 chars; no enclosing class scope); consistent with extra55's Thread.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('mappingproxy'); no prior threading spec records __dict__.__class__.__qualname__ for Thread; new to extra55"]
    - [Event_dict_class_qualname,
       Event.__dict__.__class__.__qualname__.__eq__,
       ["mappingproxy"],
       true,
       "threading.Event.__dict__.__class__.__qualname__ == 'mappingproxy' — Event's class __dict__ is a mappingproxy; the mappingproxy type is a top-level type with __qualname__ == __name__ == 'mappingproxy' (12 chars); consistent with extra55's Event.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('mappingproxy'); no prior threading spec records __dict__.__class__.__qualname__ for Event; new to extra55"]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# threading function __qualname__.__len__() — extra55
#
# threading module-level functions are pure-Python functions at the top level of
# Lib/threading.py. Their __qualname__ equals their __name__ (no enclosing
# class scope). Prior specs (extra15/extra22/extra47) confirmed the string
# equality invariants (__qualname__.__eq__) for main_thread/current_thread/
# active_count/enumerate/settrace/setprofile/stack_size, but no prior threading
# spec records __qualname__.__len__() for any of these functions as explicit
# invariant rows. The three length checks below are new to extra55.
#
# String lengths:
#   main_thread     == 11 chars (m-a-i-n-_-t-h-r-e-a-d)
#   current_thread  == 14 chars (c-u-r-r-e-n-t-_-t-h-r-e-a-d)
#   active_count    == 12 chars (a-c-t-i-v-e-_-c-o-u-n-t)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table threading_extra55.function_qualname_len:
  description: "threading function __qualname__.__len__() — main_thread(11)/current_thread(14)/active_count(12); prior specs confirmed __qualname__.__eq__ values; length dimension not recorded in any prior threading spec; new to extra55"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: method_names
  id_prefix: thrddict55

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - [main_thread_qualname_len,
       main_thread.__qualname__.__len__,
       [],
       11,
       "threading.main_thread.__qualname__.__len__() == 11 — main_thread is a pure-Python function in Lib/threading.py that returns the Thread object for the main thread; __qualname__ is 'main_thread' (11 chars: m-a-i-n-_-t-h-r-e-a-d); top-level function so __qualname__ == __name__; prior extra15/extra22/extra47 confirmed main_thread.__qualname__.__eq__('main_thread') but no prior spec records __qualname__.__len__() for main_thread; new to extra55"]
    - [current_thread_qualname_len,
       current_thread.__qualname__.__len__,
       [],
       14,
       "threading.current_thread.__qualname__.__len__() == 14 — current_thread is a pure-Python function in Lib/threading.py that returns the Thread object for the calling thread; __qualname__ is 'current_thread' (14 chars: c-u-r-r-e-n-t-_-t-h-r-e-a-d); top-level function so __qualname__ == __name__; prior extra15/extra22/extra47 confirmed current_thread.__qualname__.__eq__('current_thread') but no prior spec records __qualname__.__len__() for current_thread; new to extra55"]
    - [active_count_qualname_len,
       active_count.__qualname__.__len__,
       [],
       12,
       "threading.active_count.__qualname__.__len__() == 12 — active_count is a pure-Python function in Lib/threading.py that returns the number of Thread objects currently alive; __qualname__ is 'active_count' (12 chars: a-c-t-i-v-e-_-c-o-u-n-t); top-level function so __qualname__ == __name__; prior extra15/extra22/extra47 confirmed active_count.__qualname__.__eq__('active_count') but no prior spec records __qualname__.__len__() for active_count; new to extra55"]
